Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the
@spaghetti{180%grams}.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

When your pan of water is boiling, add the spaghetti and bring back to the boil.
Cook until tender, ~{8%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with oil and
stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on
medium-high heat. Drain the @king prawns{150%grams}.

Once hot, add the prawns and @British smoked bacon lardons{60%grams}. Stir-fry
until both are cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat and shellfish.
> Cook lardons thoroughly. Cook so the prawns are opaque in the middle.

Once the bacon and prawns are cooked, add the garlic and stir-fry until
fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @chicken stock paste{10%grams} and @water{100%milliliters} for the
sauce into the pan.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @creme fraiche{150%grams},
@peas{120%grams} and @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams}.

Add the cooked spaghetti and toss to coat in the sauce until warmed through.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add a splash of water if the sauce is
a little too thick.

Stir in the @truffle zest{1%sachet}, then remove from the heat.

Share the truffled bacon, prawn and pea spaghetti between your bowls.

Enjoy!